    "reasoning": "To implement the given Mealy FSM with one-hot encoding, we need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Identify the states: From the state transitions, we have two states: A and B. Since we use one-hot encoding, we will represent these as separate signals, say 'state_A' and 'state_B'.\n\n2. Define state transitions:\n   - From state A: if x=0, stay in A (z=0); if x=1, go to B (z=1)\n   - From state B: if x=0, stay in B (z=1); if x=1, stay in B (z=0)\n\n3. Design state register: We'll use two signals 'state_A' and 'state_B' to represent the one-hot encoded states.\n\n4. Define reset behavior: Reset is asynchronous and active high. When areset is high, the FSM should reset to state A.\n\n5. Next state logic: Based on current state and input x, determine the next state.\n\n6. Output logic: The output z is determined by the current state and input x according to the given transitions.\n\nSyntax considerations:\n- Use 'logic' for all signals.\n- Use 'always @(posedge clk)' for sequential logic.\n- Use 'always @(*)' for combinational logic.\n- Use 'if (areset)' for asynchronous reset.\n- Ensure proper initialization of state variables with initial block.\n- Use one-hot encoding: Only one state signal is high at any time.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input areset,\n    input x,\n    output z\n);\n\n    // State definitions\n    logic state_A;\n    logic state_B;\n    \n    // Next state signals\n    logic next_state_A;\n    logic next_state_B;\n    \n    // Sequential logic for state register\n    always @(posedge clk or posedge areset) begin\n        if (areset) begin\n            state_A <= 1'b1;\n            state_B <= 1'b0;\n        end\n        else begin\n            state_A <= next_state_A;\n            state_B <= next_state_B;\n        end\n    end\n    \n    // Next state logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        if (state_A) begin\n            // In state A\n            if (x) begin\n                // x=1, transition to B\n                next_state_A = 1'b0;\n                next_state_B = 1'b1;\n            end\n            else begin\n                // x=0, stay in A\n                next_state_A = 1'b1;\n                next_state_B = 1'b0;\n            end\n        end\n        else begin\n            // In state B\n            if (x) begin\n                // x=1, stay in B\n                next_state_A = 1'b0;\n                next_state_B = 1'b1;\n            end\n            else begin\n                // x=0, stay in B\n                next_state_A = 1'b0;\n                next_state_B = 1'b1;\n            end\n        end\n    end\n    \n    // Output logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        if (state_A) begin\n            // In state A\n            z = x; // z=0 when x=0, z=1 when x=1\n        end\n        else begin\n            // In state B\n            z = ~x; // z=1 when x=0, z=0 when x=1\n        end\n    end\n    \nendmodule"
